00:35:37,280 --> 00:35:40,280
He said that anything that falls

574
00:35:40,280 --> 00:35:42,280
onto the surface of a black hole,

575
00:35:42,280 --> 00:35:44,280
he said anything that falls into a black hole,

576
00:35:44,280 --> 00:35:48,280
we will come to the question of whether things do or don't fall into black holes.

577
00:35:48,280 --> 00:35:50,280
It looks from this point of view

578
00:35:50,280 --> 00:35:53,280
that it takes an infinite amount of time to fall into the black hole.

579
00:35:53,280 --> 00:35:55,280
This is a contentious question that,

580
00:35:55,280 --> 00:35:58,280
it's not contentious, it's a subtle question

581
00:35:58,280 --> 00:36:00,280
that we'll come back to.

582
00:36:00,280 --> 00:36:02,280
But for the moment, let's just think about things

583
00:36:02,280 --> 00:36:06,280
which fall onto the horizon of a black hole in this sense here.

