00:39:16,280 --> 00:39:20,280
or it can refer to the idea that it emits black body radiation.

642
00:39:20,280 --> 00:39:24,280
Black body radiation is thermal radiation, heat radiation.

643
00:39:24,280 --> 00:39:26,280
So let me just...

644
00:39:26,280 --> 00:39:33,280
So let's say that black holes are black in the sense that they emit heat radiation.

645
00:39:33,280 --> 00:39:39,280
It was thought earlier that black holes were black in the sense that they emitted no radiation.

646
00:39:39,280 --> 00:39:47,280
So we need to come to an understanding of what it was that made Hawking, Bekenstein,

647
00:39:47,280 --> 00:39:52,280
other people think that black holes have some heat in them.

648
00:39:52,280 --> 00:39:53,280
They're not completely dead.

649
00:39:53,280 --> 00:39:55,280
They have some heat.

650
00:39:55,280 --> 00:39:58,280
Because they have some heat, they glow.

651
00:39:58,280 --> 00:40:00,280
Because they glow, they give off light.

652
00:40:00,280 --> 00:40:05,280
Because they give off light or radiation, they give off energy.

653
00:40:05,280 --> 00:40:09,280
That means with time, their energy must decrease.

654
00:40:09,280 --> 00:40:13,280
Well, energy and mass are the same thing, E equals mc squared.

655
00:40:13,280 --> 00:40:19,280
And so with time, the mass should decrease as it gives off this radiation.

656
00:40:19,280 --> 00:40:22,280
And if the mass decreases,

657
00:40:22,280 --> 00:40:26,280
then the Schwarzschild radius, 2mg, decreases.

658
00:40:26,280 --> 00:40:36,280
And one should expect in time, if black holes really do have some active heat in them,

